content:
When integrating Data Cloud and Marketing Cloud Engagement, clearly delineate the roles and responsibilities between each product. Data Cloud is designed to ingest, resolve, transform, segment, and enrich data. Marketing Cloud Engagement is an engagement product that orchestrates personalized messaging campaigns.

We recommend taking time to examine the data foundation that you create in the Engagement Contact Model. To balance and increase marketer efficiency while preventing data sprawl in Engagement, we recommend an initial data foundation that selectively integrates a commonly shared dataset.

The data foundation in Engagement stores unified customer profiles and is used as the central point of truth for customer data. You can model your data foundation using either the Core Audience Model or the Collective Core Audience Model, depending on the size and complexity of your organization.

In the Core Audience Model, you create two activations in Data Cloud: one at the Individual level and one at the Unified Individual level. Each activation contains your organization's full active audience and required content personalization and decisioning attributes.

In the Collective Core Audience Model, you group commonly shared attributes into 2-15 categories. For each category, create a separate activation in Data Cloud that includes all the required content personalization and decisioning attributes. Then, link the resulting data extensions to the Engagement Contact Model in a 1:1 relationship.

To model your data foundation, determine the best model for your organization's needs, initialize your data foundation by activating core audiences to Engagement, and establish your data foundation by connecting the resulting data extensions to the Engagement Contact Model.
title: Establishing a Data Foundation for Marketing Cloud Engagement
